n getResource and not in getResources. I wonder if Flyway calls getResource in this context. There's a lot to untangle here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating resource scanning**\\n\\nI'm noticing that if `NativeDetector` is true, it enters the next step, and if `scanner.getResource` returns non-null, line 86 won't be reached. The problem seems to be with what was uncovered before encountering \\\"no provider.\\\" To ensure that `scanner.getResource` returns null, I should probably select a classpath resource that's outside the Flyway locations. This should help clarify what’s going wrong in the process.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nhj3b2CYz13k02ayQPokQSeE|fc_09a1be87b3b073c2016a41b7504880819086b3450309d124f8", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find ~/.gradle -name 'Flyway.class' | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3145, "output": 2009, "cacheRead": 56832, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 61986, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782691635193, "responseId": "resp_09a1be87b3b073c2016a41b733f6788190b8f6c1c9f0aef3a2"}}
