nn3rB5vhh9KsJjBHVbaQckbonL7RyoZkiQtroqVhqA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test and metadata issues**\\n\\nI'm looking at a situation where a test is untracked and not showing up in the diff stat. There’s also the question of whether we need to worry about untracked metadata being included in the review. I think we might need to use a git command to view the status of the file. There's a potential issue with a test we've written that sets an internal bean class, which may not align with public API expectations. I could adjust phrasing, but we might not need to. Perhaps improving the code comments could help clarify things.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing bean definition and dependencies**\\n\\nI’m considering a simpler approach using pattern matching in Java 21, like `if (!(beanFactory instanceof BeanDefinitionRegistry registry)) throw new IllegalStateException`. This could reduce AssertJ use in the infrastructure. I wonder if there's any missing metadata for assertion classes in native environments. It seems we shouldn't directly reflect on certain classes, and there might be implications with setting parameters like `factoryBeanName`. I'm also thinking about adding platform dependencies, possibly requiring `spring-boot-autoconfigure` for consistency across libraries. The hardcoded H2 version needs attention too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying source root for tests**\\n\\nI’m looking into the source root for the target test. Although it seems the source root is not explicitly stated, it's likely that \\\"tests/src\\\" is the correct directory. I want to ensure everything is concise and clear in this context. So, confirming that this path leads to the necessary files would help solidify my understanding and keep things straightforward. Making this explicit provides clarity moving forward.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.springframework.boot.flyway.autoconfigure.NativeImageResourceProvider`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-flyway/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_flyway/NativeImageResourceProviderTest.java`\n  - Uses Spring Boot `FlywayAutoConfiguration` with a real H2 `DataSource`.\n  - Runs the default `classpath:db/migration` migration script.\n  - Asserts the migration created data and was recorded in Flyway schema history.\n  - Resolves the migration through Flyway’s configured `ResourceProvider`, exercising the native-image resource-provider path.\n- Updated `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-flyway/4.0.6/build.gradle`\n  - Switched `spring-boot-autoconfigure` to `$libraryVersion`.\n  - Added `spring-boot-test:$libraryVersion` for `ApplicationContextRunner`.\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09a1be87b3b073c2016a41b787ab9c81909513a13ce4c7875e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1515, "output": 687, "cacheRead": 65024, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 67226, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782691707960, "responseId": "resp_09a1be87b3b073c2016a41b77ccb648190b54849b60c22eae4"}, "toolResults": []}
