naged to do that before, even when null assertions were involved. I'm thinking that yes, it is possible. Now, I need to solidify this into a clear final answer! Let's keep this concise, as I want to ensure clarity in my response. It's a bit technical, but I think I've got it figured out.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated `NativeImageResourceProviderTest` so the explicit resource lookup exercises the native-image branch on the JVM too.\n\nKey fix:\n- Sets `org.graalvm.nativeimage.imagecode=runtime` before creating the `ApplicationContextRunner`.\n- Creates the context runner lazily after setting the property, so `NativeDetector` sees the native-image mode.\n- Keeps the migration/resource assertion, which should now return a non-null `LoadableResource` instead of delegating to the scanner-only JVM branch.\n\nFiles changed:\n- `tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-flyway/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_flyway/NativeImageResourceProviderTest.java`\n\nNo tests were run locally, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09a1be87b3b073c2016a41b837dcd08190907ec8fd9b5673cc\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2349, "output": 708, "cacheRead": 65536, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 68593, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782691883231, "responseId": "resp_09a1be87b3b073c2016a41b82c459c81908db9204ee1baa920"}, "toolResults": []}
